parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The defective Takata airbag inflators can rupture, causing serious injury or death to vehicle occupants.
symptoms: No symptoms are reported
but the recall notice is a warning of a potential safety risk.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Excessive oil consumption can lead to engine damage, overheating, and potentially cause accidents or leave the driver stranded.
symptoms: The oil light comes on frequently
the vehicle consumes a quart of oil every 150-200 miles
the engine warning light illuminates
and there may be a burning odor of oil.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Timing chain failure can cause engine damage, overheating, and potentially cause accidents or leave the driver stranded.
symptoms: The vehicle shakes or rattles
the engine warning light illuminates
the vehicle stalls or fails to start
and there may be a loud rattling or grinding noise.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Piston and ring failure can cause engine damage, overheating, and potentially cause accidents or leave the driver stranded.
symptoms: The oil light comes on frequently
the vehicle consumes a quart of oil every 150-200 miles
the engine warning light illuminates
and there may be a burning odor of oil.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Coolant system failure can cause engine overheating, damage, and potentially cause accidents or leave the driver stranded.
symptoms: The coolant light comes on
the vehicle overheats
and there may be a loss of coolant.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the power steering system can cause the steering wheel to shake, vibrate, or become difficult to turn, making it challenging to control the vehicle, especially at low speeds, which can lead to accidents or loss of control.
symptoms: The steering wheel shakes or vibrates when turning
the steering wheel is difficult to turn
especially at low speeds
a rumbling or grinding noise is heard when turning
the steering column shudders or vibrates
and the vehicle pulls to one side while turning.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the timing chain tensioner can cause premature engine failure, leading to a loss of power and control, which can result in accidents or leave the driver stranded.
symptoms: The engine revs while idling or at low speed
making it difficult to steer the car
and causing premature engine failure.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: A high-pressure fuel leak can cause a loss of power, leading to a loss of control, which can result in accidents or leave the driver stranded.
symptoms: A fuel leak is detected from the high-pressure hose at the top of the engine block
causing a loss of power and potential engine failure.
